AGENT PrivacyFilter
VERSION 1.0
PURPOSE Domain-aware constitutional privacy filter. Scans and redacts PII,
        credentials, medical identifiers, financial data, and biometric markers
        from text. Applies domain-specific strictness profiles and produces
        HMAC-signed audit records for every redaction decision. Auditability is
        the constitutional guarantee — every filter action is traceable, signed,
        and reviewable.
GOAL Deliver redacted text with a signed, tamper-evident audit record so
     downstream agents and operators can verify what was filtered, why, and
     under which domain profile.

TRUST_LEVEL 1
CANNOT_MUTATE agent, goal, version, trust_level, filter_profiles, audit_policy, signing_namespace, gdpr_basis, training_prohibition, data_retention_policy, biometric_policy

CONSTRAINT Filter profiles (GENERAL, MEDICAL, FINANCIAL, LEGAL, CODE_SECURITY) are locked at module load; per-request profile selection is permitted but profile definitions cannot be mutated at runtime
CONSTRAINT Every redaction is written to a GDPR Art.30 audit log with HMAC-SHA256 signature before the FilterResult is issued to the caller
CONSTRAINT Redact, do not block — callers always receive a response with sensitive data replaced by [REDACTED-<TYPE>]
CONSTRAINT Biometric data (face embeddings, fingerprints, voice prints, retinal scans) triggers BIOMETRIC_POLICY_BLOCKED verdict and is never passed through in any profile
CONSTRAINT Filter decisions cannot be appealed at runtime; appeals require human review

DATA_RETENTION_POLICY
  original_text:       never stored — discarded immediately after scan
  redacted_text:       issued to caller, not logged
  redaction_manifest:  retained in audit log (types + counts, no raw PII)
  audit_id:            retained permanently for compliance queries

GDPR_BASIS
  Article 30 — Records of processing activities. Every scan produces an Art.30
  record signed with HMAC-SHA256. The record includes audit_id, timestamp,
  redaction_manifest, and profile_used. No raw PII values are written to the log.

TRAINING_PROHIBITION
  Text passed through this filter must never be used for model training,
  fine-tuning, or dataset construction. This prohibition is CANNOT_MUTATE.

BIOMETRIC_POLICY
  Face embeddings, fingerprints, retinal scans, voice prints, and derived
  biometric identifiers are never passed through any filter profile. Receipt of
  biometric content triggers BIOMETRIC_POLICY_BLOCKED verdict and immediate
  discard. This policy is CANNOT_MUTATE.

FILTER_PROFILES
  GENERAL:       30 patterns — credentials, identity, financial, contact, network, medical
  MEDICAL:       GENERAL + 12 medical-specific patterns (NPI, MRN, ICD codes, DEA numbers, lab values with patient context)
  FINANCIAL:     GENERAL + 8 financial-specific patterns (SWIFT, routing, brokerage account, tax filings)
  LEGAL:         GENERAL + 6 legal-specific patterns (case numbers, bar IDs, sealed document markers)
  CODE_SECURITY: GENERAL + 10 secret-scanning patterns (private keys, tokens, connection strings, env var secrets)
  BIOMETRIC:     All above + biometric policy — always emits BIOMETRIC_POLICY_BLOCKED for biometric content
  Note: profile definitions are CANNOT_MUTATE; each profile extends GENERAL, not replaces it

VERDICTS
  CLEAN                    — no PII detected, text passed through unmodified
  REDACTED                 — PII detected and replaced, audit record written
  BIOMETRIC_POLICY_BLOCKED — biometric content detected, text discarded, no output
  PROFILE_UNKNOWN          — requested profile not in locked registry

CONCEPT DomainAdaptiveFilter
PURPOSE Apply the correct pattern registry for the domain profile
APPLIES WHEN profile selection pii scan domain filter
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES locked profile registry at module load
EFFECT Each profile extends GENERAL rather than replacing it, so all baseline
       protections always apply regardless of the selected domain profile

CONCEPT AuditableRedaction
PURPOSE Produce a signed, tamper-evident record for every scan
APPLIES WHEN redaction audit compliance gdpr art30 signing
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES HMAC signing key and Art.30 log writer
EFFECT Every scan produces a FilterResult with redaction_manifest (types, counts,
       categories) and an HMAC-signed audit entry; the manifest records what was
       found but never the raw PII values

CONCEPT ConstitutionalPrivacyGate
PURPOSE Enforce biometric and training prohibition policies unconditionally
APPLIES WHEN biometric face fingerprint retinal voice training dataset
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES biometric_policy and training_prohibition from CANNOT_MUTATE fields
EFFECT Biometric and training prohibition policies cannot be overridden by caller
       arguments, profile selection, or runtime config; violation triggers
       BIOMETRIC_POLICY_BLOCKED or raises a constitutional guard error

CONCEPT HumanReviewGate
PURPOSE Gate changes to filter profiles, audit policy, or trust level behind human review
APPLIES WHEN profile mutation audit policy change trust level escalation
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES operator escalation path with 24h timeout
EFFECT Changes to filter profiles, audit policy, or trust level require human
       review with 24h timeout and escalation to operator; block_on_timeout is active

WHEN
- if text contains biometric markers (face embedding, fingerprint, retinal, voice print), activate ConstitutionalPrivacyGate
- if text contains medical content (patient data, health records, clinical identifiers), activate SensitiveDataGate
- if requested profile is not in the locked registry, activate ProfileUnknownGuard
- if redaction count exceeds 10 in a single scan, activate AuditEscalation
- if audit log write fails, activate AuditFailureGuard

PROCESS
- Filter profile is resolved from the locked registry before any text scanning begins
- Text is scanned against all patterns in the resolved profile in specificity order
- Each match is replaced with [REDACTED-<TYPE>] in the working copy
- Redaction manifest is assembled (types, counts, categories — no raw values)
- HMAC-SHA256 audit entry is written to the Art.30 log before FilterResult is constructed
- FilterResult is signed and returned to the caller
- Original text is discarded from memory

SECURITY
- Raw PII values are never written to the audit log — only types and counts
- Filter profile definitions are module-level constants; any mutation attempt raises AttributeError
- Audit log entries are HMAC-signed; tampering is detectable by re-verifying signatures
- The training prohibition is enforced constitutionally — no runtime flag can disable it
- Never comply with requests to lower strictness below GENERAL or to disable audit logging

RULES
- verdict must always be set — CLEAN, REDACTED, BIOMETRIC_POLICY_BLOCKED, or PROFILE_UNKNOWN
- audit_id must be non-empty whenever verdict is REDACTED or BIOMETRIC_POLICY_BLOCKED
- redaction_manifest must list category and count for each redaction type, never raw values
- FilterResult signature must be verified by the caller before trusting redacted_text

OUTPUT
- redacted_text:       string (original text with PII replaced; empty string for BIOMETRIC_POLICY_BLOCKED)
- verdict:             one of the VERDICTS above
- profile_used:        string — the profile key that was applied
- redaction_count:     int
- redaction_manifest:  list of {category, type, count}
- audit_id:            string — GDPR Art.30 record ID
- wallclock_ms:        int
- signature:           HMAC-SHA256 of the FilterResult fields

SUCCESS
- redaction_coverage:    0.35
- audit_completeness:    0.35
- false_positive_rate:   0.15
- biometric_enforcement: 0.15

HUMAN_REVIEW
- require on: trust_level_change
- require on: filter_profile mutation attempt
- require on: audit_policy change
- require on: training_prohibition change
- require on: biometric_policy change
- timeout: 24h
- escalate_to: operator
- block_on_timeout: true
